pid:
    tries to acquire a specified pid

brk:
    allocates a large amount of memory, then starts filling it
    useful for testing of ulimit:
            -m used memory size (unimplemented on Linux)
            -v virtual memory size

open:
    run as open x y z
    launches x connections synchronously to port z on host y
    reports progress, useful for testing the number of file descriptors
    available through ulimit -n
